<br>
These specs are similar to the basic warrior spec...<br>
<br>
50 Axe/Hammer/Sword<br>
42 Shield<br>
39 Parry<br>
<br>
I did a Warrior/Mercenary comparison just so that you realize the difference between the two classes speCCed defensively.<br>
<br>
Armor - <br>
Same: Both wear chain<br>
<br>
Hit Points - <br>
Same: Pure melee hit point tables <br>
<br>
Special ability -  <br>
Mercenary: actually has three <br>
Flurry/Dirty tricks/Enchance Evaded<br>
<br>
Warrior: has nothing, no tricks.<br>
<br>
DMG capability - <br>
Mercenary: better styles then warrior has, and a second weapon that has chance to go off.<br>
                    <br>
Warrior: has weakest 2h styled dmg of all realms.  The 2h dmg is still weaker then low specced dual wield.  They both have the same 1h style dmg. <br>
<br>
Shield - <br>
Mercenary: can use Medium/Small shields which are most often the best, and can switch out shield for a left handed weapon so they can dual wield again much like warrior switching but the dual wield is stronger then warrior 2h.<br>
<br>
Warrior: can use large shields and gets to have 1h/2h in same spec.  Most warriors use medium or small shield however.  The 2h dmg is so much weaker then merc DW that its not worth switching because of defense loss of shield<br>
<br>
Realm abilities - <br>
<br>
Both get same RA's except warrior has mastery of blocking, and mercenary has dodger.  I would say dodger works more then blocking and is more useful in rvr especially with enchanced evade on mercs, plus blocking won't work for warrior if he is using 2h and dodger works while merc is dual wielding or using sword and board and all around him because of enchanced evade.<br>
<br>
Overall:  I think Mercenary is the better defense tank and has a lot more fluff.  If you don't think this would be a good spec then I guess the warriors need alot of love since this is what they are but with less fluff/dmg then yourselves, and really have no other options to spec then this way.<br>
<br>
<br>
