<br>
I've rarely used my shield. The only time I've ever equiped it is running out solo in the frontier and then its done absolutely no good (5 infils&gt;&gt;shield BM). Only other time I've equiped it is when running a ram on a keep. Besides that, the shield is just an extra weight to carry around. Well, it does serve one purpose. It makes a nice sled to drag my dead corpse on. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Raeloran Twinblade</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, 48 Blademaster, Legendary Grandmaster Armorcrafter, Pellinor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrecsnowmane>Kerrec Snowmane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#000000>(3/13/03 5:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=131.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What do mercenaries think of these specs?</span><hr size=1> 3 things to say:<br>
<br>
1) Spending points.  This is my personal opinion, but spending points in abilities that negate themselves is counterproductive.  What I mean is, when you're using a shield, your points invested in DW are unused, wasted.  When you're dual wielding, your points invested in Shield are unused, wasted.  This would be considered a &quot;Jack of all Trades&quot; spec in any other class.  All nice when you have Chants, Stealth, Enhance, etc etc to choose from, but not so when all you have is damage or defense.  <br>
<br>
2) If you choose Thrust as your weapon spec, you absolutely need lvl 50 DW for the STYLE.  Thrust is nearly as poor as the DW line.  DW should be spec'd to AT LEAST 44 because it increases your chance to double attack, but mostly because the ONLY worthy styles of the line are Reflection and Hypnotic Darkness (stun style chain ).  50 DW when spec'd thrust is something I'm adamant about.  Look at the available styles...<br>
<br>
3) Defense.  It works 1 vs 1.  It doesn't work 8 vs. 8  Go look in the logs section...I have plenty of solo fights in there and you can see Evade/Parry working.  Then take a look at the few group battles, and it's gone.<br>
<br>
All that aside, I have to say I'm impressed that you wrote a post that wasn't an outright flame.  Hope to see more discussion from you, and less provocative threads. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>M.C. Hammah</span><br>  Posts: 259<br> <font color=#000000>(3/13/03 8:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=131.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What do mercenaries think of these specs?</span><hr size=1> Some very valid points Kerrec, I do have a couple points of contention though.<br>
<br>
1. Shield is a weapon - defense is just a bonus <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Yeah, I know, it really is for defense, but an anytime stun is very potent <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>offense</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
2. Yes, higher DW does increase chance to swing offhand  - but not by all that much.  Speccing shield takes away the NEED to spec thrust to 50, or DW to 44 for the stun styles, cuz you get an ANYTIME stun style.  It replaces the need to rely on a reactionary - which yer not gonna get in group combat - with a clumsy inventory switch.<br>
<br>
Is it worth it to give up a little damage and weaponskill?  I can't really say for sure yet, but I'm gonna give it a whirl soon as I can.  My personal opinion is that mercs should have the OPTION to spec shield, but our damage should be higher, and defense fixed in GROUP/ZERG combat ... ya know, what the game is all about. <p>Nirala HammahMastah<br>
&lt;The Kindred&gt;<br>
50 Hammah-wielding, chaos creating, caster bashing Merc of Gawaine. </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kiamarvigilance>Kiamar Vigilance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#000000>(3/14/03 12:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=131.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What do mercenaries think of these specs?</span><hr size=1> Notice how Protoss neglects to mention that Mercs can't hotkey Shields and then Dual-weild? Also, Warriors actually have the HIGHEST base damage output out of any melee class so he is incorrect in assuming that S/S Mercs will outdamage warriors. While I'm on a roll, need I mention the fact that Warriors don't need to Dual-spec so they can pump more skillpoints into Parry?<br>
<br>
Warriors get versitility since they can easily switch from defensive to offensive orientation. Mercs who try speccing Shield reduce their damage output and also their parry because they have to spec both slash/thrust/crush and Dual-weild. A merc who specs shield 42+, is basically a Warrior who can't hotkey sheild, inflicts LESS damage than a Warrior and parries significantly less than a Warrior. In return, they get Dirt on a 30 minute timer, Flurry (100-150 damage every 2 minutes), Charge, and Advanced Evade 1 instead of Evade 1 (whoop-dee-do).<br>
<br>
To summarize, a 42+ Shield-specced Merc is a bad spec when compared to the alternatives. You become a 1-trick pony with fluffy timered abilities. A Hybrid Polearmsmen is way more viable. More damage output and you can actually hotkey shield.<br>
<br>
Sure, there will be people who try this spec out for its uniqueness. However, you will probably never see this spec in high-end (rank 6+) RVR unless Mythic makes some changes like allowing shield to be hotkeyed into the 2-hand slot.<br>
<br>
